    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Luis Robert Jr.** anchoring the offense as our highest-rated start at 73.98. Facing a favorable matchup against Eduardo Rodriguez, **Luis Robert Jr.** benefits from a significant 14% platoon boost and a prime #3 hole assignment, making him our primary engine for power and speed. **Jacob Wilson** follows closely with a 66.74 score; his leadoff role against the left-handed Ryan Weathers provides a clear path to production, buoyed by a 4% park factor upgrade. While **Jackson Merrill** (60.31) remains a recommended start due to his high-leverage order position, **Miguel Vargas** sits on the cusp at 56.83. The decision to start **Miguel Vargas** despite a sub-60 score reflects his consistent spot in the lineup, though his output is slightly tempered by the presence of a tough hold pitcher in Seth Lugo who suppresses the stolen base upside we prioritize.\n\n**Liam Hicks** presents our most volatile profile at 41.33, narrowly clearing the threshold for inclusion. His base projection is hampered by the high-skill arm of Brandon Lowder (3.31 xERA), but a dynamic platoon advantage against the right-hander and his cleanup status keep him in the fold to manage our daily game cap efficiency. The bench remains quiet today, as heavy hitters like **Kyle Tucker**, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, and **Gunnar Henderson** are all unavailable due to scheduled off-days. With depth pieces like **Andy Pages**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, and **Coby Mayo** also absent from the active rotation, our strategy focuses on maximizing the ceiling of our five active starters. We are monitoring for any late-breaking lineup changes, but as it stands, the combination of **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jacob Wilson** provides the best opportunity to gain ground in the stolen base category, which remains our league-wide competitive imperative.",
